197
00:22:09,068 --> 00:22:12,241
It's all the way across the
city. Fenced off at sides.

198
00:22:13,758 --> 00:22:15,758
Try a nice trip
to the zoo, instead?

199
00:22:15,827 --> 00:22:17,793
But it's a matter
of life and death.

200
00:22:17,862 --> 00:22:20,310
These days everything
is a matter of life and death.

201
00:22:20,379 --> 00:22:21,448
But..

202
00:22:21,517 --> 00:22:24,344
Pardon me, lady.
I got business to do.

203
00:22:32,862 --> 00:22:36,689
[announcement on PA]
'Bulletin 5-1-3-7-8.'

204
00:22:36,758 --> 00:22:39,344
'Remember, the system
is your friend.'

205
00:22:39,413 --> 00:22:42,137
'You help us,
and we'll help you.'

206
00:22:42,206 --> 00:22:44,344
'Report suspicious behavior.'

207
00:22:44,413 --> 00:22:46,482
'Don't let
the traitors steal from you'

208
00:22:46,551 --> 00:22:48,655
'what is rightfully yours.'

209
00:22:48,724 --> 00:22:52,931
'End Bulletin 5-1-3-7-8.'

210
00:22:57,931 --> 00:23:00,206
[thud]

211
00:23:02,172 --> 00:23:03,655
[dramatic music]

212
00:23:05,896 --> 00:23:07,724
[thunder rumbling]

213
00:23:13,068 --> 00:23:15,000
[beeping]

214
00:23:26,344 --> 00:23:28,827
[beeping]

215
00:23:33,137 --> 00:23:35,551
[music continues]

216
00:23:54,448 --> 00:23:56,344
Back again, Austin?

217
00:23:58,413 --> 00:24:00,344
- How you doin'?
- I'll take that.

218
00:24:00,413 --> 00:24:01,965
Yeah.

219
00:24:07,068 --> 00:24:08,482
Go ahead.

220
00:24:09,310 --> 00:24:11,896
Well, well, well.

221
00:24:11,965 --> 00:24:15,172
If it isn't my dear
old friend, Austin.

222
00:24:16,172 --> 00:24:19,862
Tell me. How is life
treating you?

223
00:24:19,931 --> 00:24:22,103
Same as everyone.
Like a turd in a toilet.

224
00:24:23,896 --> 00:24:26,793
Got something for you, I think
you're gonna like, Akmir.

225
00:24:33,206 --> 00:24:36,724
- Where did you find this?
- Just gotta know where to look.

226
00:24:36,793 --> 00:24:39,310
You must look for a fresh cigar.

227
00:24:39,379 --> 00:24:41,448
For this I will
trade handsomely.

228
00:24:43,655 --> 00:24:47,172
In the meanwhile...what
do you wish for these batteries?

229
00:24:48,586 --> 00:24:50,482
Three RZB sounds fair.

230
00:24:51,068 --> 00:24:52,724
Fair?

231
00:24:54,068 --> 00:24:58,241
I tell you fair.
Four batteries for one RZB.

232
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:04,310
Alright, Akmir.
Three for two.

233
00:25:04,379 --> 00:25:06,482
And next time we'll
talk about the cigar.

234
00:25:06,551 --> 00:25:10,068
Three for one.
My final offer.

235
00:25:10,137 --> 00:25:12,655
I'll give you
all the RZB you want.

236
00:25:12,724 --> 00:25:14,931
- Who is this bitch?
- You got me.

237
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:18,379
How dare you come
into Akmir's place to trade?

238
00:25:18,448 --> 00:25:20,896
What is in this deal,
for Mr.Akmir?

239
00:25:24,758 --> 00:25:26,620
Take cover.

240
00:25:27,344 --> 00:25:28,620
[groans]

241
00:25:37,862 --> 00:25:40,034
I want the female.

242
00:25:47,275 --> 00:25:52,517
You are not alone, my friend.
Many people want a girl.

243
00:25:52,586 --> 00:25:55,000
She is an exquisite
creature, yes?

244
00:25:56,206 --> 00:26:01,000
But tell me.
What you offer in trade. Huh?

245
00:26:03,482 --> 00:26:05,758
[groaning]

246
00:26:05,827 --> 00:26:07,724
Get the hell outta here!

247
00:26:07,793 --> 00:26:09,344
Aa-h-h.

248
00:26:14,379 --> 00:26:16,724
[intense music]

249
00:26:45,137 --> 00:26:47,206
[music continues]

250
00:26:51,655 --> 00:26:53,137
Argh.

251
00:27:03,034 --> 00:27:05,172
Identify yourself.

252
00:27:13,448 --> 00:27:16,000
[spluttering]

253
00:27:24,965 --> 00:27:26,275
Whoa.

254
00:27:34,413 --> 00:27:36,931
Why didn't you tell
there was a cyborg chasing you?

255
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:39,724
Didn't have a chance. Tried
to tell someone was after me.

256
00:27:39,793 --> 00:27:42,000
Not just someone. A killing
machine. Their newest model.

257
00:27:42,068 --> 00:27:44,172
Please. I need
to get to the port.

258
00:27:45,344 --> 00:27:47,068
[static]

259
00:27:47,137 --> 00:27:49,068
[thunder rumbling]

260
00:28:12,965 --> 00:28:15,103
[thunder rumbling]

261
00:28:18,034 --> 00:28:20,689
[thunder rumbling]

262
00:28:20,758 --> 00:28:23,413
Alright. So what's the story?
Why is he chasing you?

263
00:28:23,482 --> 00:28:25,379
I've got something he wants.

264
00:28:25,448 --> 00:28:27,206
